### Test Authentication Flow

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5075/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "confirmPassword": "password123"
}

### 2. Login with the registered user
POST http://localhost:5075/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get current user info (use the token from login response)
GET http://localhost:5075/api/user/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Logout (use the same token)
POST http://localhost:5075/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "YOUR_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 5. Validate token (should fail after logout)
POST http://localhost:5075/api/auth/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "YOUR_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 6. Test with invalid token
POST http://localhost:5075/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "invalid_token_here"
} 